trend_summary: Images show steady infill: warehouses proliferate along the highway, commercial blocks fill central gaps, and cul-de-sac housing thickens. The built footprint hardly spreads outward, yet internal lots, roads and parking expand, trimming some tree cover. Overall, a maturing suburban corridor shifts toward medium-density mixed use.
notable_changes: New warehouses and logistics buildings added along the north-west industrial strip.
Primary highway widened with extra ramps and frontage roads.
Vacant central parcels converted to low-rise commercial and townhouse developments.
Tree canopy slightly reduced, especially near new transport and building sites.
Expanded parking areas replace older structures around shopping and office clusters.
